nimation":true,"section_padding":"section--vertical-padding-none"}},"f174083d-86a1-45d8-839d-cd2ff360c0ca":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--15838849040437__f174083d-86a1-45d8-839d-cd2ff360c0ca-text-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>The business went from a small beginning to a full-time effort. Joanie began to put more energy into the line, and her sister, Barbara, fully managed the business logistics side of things. Together, they've made PONO what it is today - although fluid and evolving daily. <strong>\"You can't hold a tight grip on an art business because the nature of art is fluidity,\" says Joanie.<\/strong> They are an incredible duo rich in love and talent. <\/p><p>\"Our products are made of a \"forever resin,\" and the pieces are of real value – they are increasingly made of plant-based resin,\" says Joanie. \"They are meant to be worn with something as simple and every day as a white t-shirt if you want. It needs to be useful in your daily life.\" She goes on to share that she had no heirlooms from her mother or grandmother passed down. She reflects, \"I want our clients to hand down PONO jewelry. This is not a single-use piece of jewelry. It's a gift to give – and pass on to whoever, whenever. It's all about the connection and the collector's spirit.\" <\/p><p><strong>PONO is the Hawaiian word for righteousness, quality, goodness, and virtuousness in perfect order. <\/strong><\/p><p>Joanie is PONO. <\/p>","text_font_class":"fs-body-100"}}},"block_order":["template--15838849040437__f174083d-86a1-45d8-839d-cd2ff360c0ca-text-1"],"settings":{"alignment":"left_left","enable_animation":true,"divider_style":"none","section_padding":"section--vertical-padding-top-bottom","content_width":"custom","custom_content_width":700}},"43248247-e002-49ae-ab50-f5e52522a06b":{"type":"image-hero-split","blocks":{"template--15376799727669__43248247-e002-49ae-ab50-f5e52522a06b-1668222967ce8aad84-0":{"type":"image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Sc